Class ModelBuilderVisitor

java.lang.Object

      com.csvanefalk.keytestgen.core.model.implementation.ModelBuilderVisitor
All Implemented Interfaces:
de.uka.ilkd.key.logic.Visitor
 class ModelBuilderVisitor
extends KeYTestGenTermVisitor

This Visitor walks a Term and extracts information related to the program variables represented in the term. The goal of this procedure is to provide sufficient information for later constructing a Model including the extracted variables.

Author:
christopher

parseVariableTerm

private void parseVariableTerm(de.uka.ilkd.key.logic.Term term)
Parse a Term representing a program variable. Such a Term can be either a plain local declaration (i.e. a LocationVariable ), or it can be part of a nested hierarchy (i.e. a SortDependingFunction). We treat both cases here.

Parameters:
term - the term to parse

visit

public void visit(de.uka.ilkd.key.logic.Term visited)
Visit a Term node, extracting any data related to ProgramVariable instances in this node, if any. If such data is found, it will be encoded in a ModelVariable format.

IMPORTANT: Due to how Term ASTs are implemented, this method will only have the desired effect if the visitation is carried out in postorder. Preorder will cause the Model to be constructed with wrong parent-child relationships.

To achieve correct results, thus, please only pass this visitor as a parameter to Term.execPostOrder(de.uka.ilkd.key.logic.Visitor)
